### `@property` — Getter Without Parentheses

```python
class Dataset:
    def __init__(self, data):
        self._data = data

    @property
    def shape(self):
        return len(self._data), len(self._data[0])

ds = Dataset([[1, 2], [3, 4], [5, 6]])
print(ds.shape)   # (3, 2) — accessed like an attribute, not a method
```

