### `@staticmethod` vs `@classmethod`

```python
class Preprocessor:
    scaler = "StandardScaler"

    @staticmethod
    def normalize(x):
        # No access to class or instance — pure utility
        return (x - min(x)) / (max(x) - min(x))

    @classmethod
    def get_scaler(cls):
        # Access to class via cls — not the instance
        return cls.scaler

print(Preprocessor.normalize([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]))
print(Preprocessor.get_scaler())   # StandardScaler
```

> 💡 **Rule of thumb:**
> - Use `@staticmethod` when the method doesn't need the class or instance at all
> - Use `@classmethod` when the method needs to read or modify class-level data

