## 3. List Comprehensions

> One-liner replacement for `for` loops — faster, cleaner, more Pythonic.

**Syntax:**
```
[expression   for item in iterable   if condition]
```

---

### Basic Examples

```python
# Squares of 1 to 10
squares      = [x ** 2 for x in range(1, 11)]

# Even squares only
even_squares = [x ** 2 for x in range(1, 11) if x % 2 == 0]
# [4, 16, 36, 64, 100]

# Ternary inside comprehension
labels       = ["pass" if x >= 0.75 else "fail" for x in [0.9, 0.6, 0.8, 0.5]]
# ['pass', 'fail', 'pass', 'fail']
```

---

### ML-Flavoured Examples

```python
features = [0.5, -0.3, 1.2, -0.8, 0.9, 0.0]

# ReLU activation
relu_out   = [max(0, x) for x in features]
# [0.5, 0, 1.2, 0, 0.9, 0]

# Min-max normalisation
mn, mx     = min(features), max(features)
normalised = [round((x - mn) / (mx - mn), 4) for x in features]

# High-confidence feature names
high_conf  = [f"feature_{i}" for i, x in enumerate(features) if abs(x) > 0.5]
# ['feature_0', 'feature_2', 'feature_4']
```

---

### Nested List Comprehension

```python
matrix     = [[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6], [7, 8, 9]]

# Flatten 2D → 1D
flat       = [val for row in matrix for val in row]
# [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9]

# Transpose
transposed = [[row[i] for row in matrix] for i in range(len(matrix[0]))]
# [[1,4,7], [2,5,8], [3,6,9]]
```

---

### Dict, Set & Generator Comprehensions

```python
labels    = ["cat", "dog", "bird", "fish"]

# Dict comprehension — label → index (like a tokeniser vocab)
label2idx = {label: idx for idx, label in enumerate(labels)}
idx2label = {idx: label for label, idx in label2idx.items()}
# {'cat': 0, 'dog': 1, 'bird': 2, 'fish': 3}

# Set comprehension — unique values
raw_tags   = ["nlp", "ml", "nlp", "cv", "ml", "ai"]
unique     = {tag for tag in raw_tags}
# {'nlp', 'ml', 'cv', 'ai'}

# Generator expression — memory efficient, no list in RAM
total      = sum(x ** 2 for x in range(1_000_000))
```

> 💡 Use a **generator** `()` instead of a list `[]` when working with large datasets —
> it processes one item at a time without loading everything into memory.

