## ⚡ Quick Cheatsheet

```
OOP
├── class MyClass:                  → define a class
├── def __init__(self, ...):        → constructor
├── self.attr = value               → instance variable
├── ClassName.attr = value          → class variable
├── @property                       → getter as attribute
├── @staticmethod                   → utility, no self/cls
├── @classmethod                    → gets cls, not self
└── super().__init__(...)           → call parent constructor

FUNCTIONS
├── def func(*args, **kwargs):      → flexible signature
├── lambda x: expr                  → anonymous one-liner
├── map(fn, iterable)               → apply fn to all
├── filter(fn, iterable)            → keep where fn True
├── reduce(fn, iterable)            → collapse to 1 value
└── @decorator                      → wrap a function

LIST COMPREHENSIONS
├── [expr for x in it]              → basic
├── [expr for x in it if cond]      → filtered
├── [a if c else b for x in it]     → ternary
├── [x for row in mat for x in row] → flatten
├── {k: v for k, v in pairs}        → dict comp
├── {x for x in it}                 → set comp
└── (x for x in it)                 → generator (no list)
```

