## 😕 Confusion Point

- `@staticmethod` vs `@classmethod` — both called on the class without an instance, but `@classmethod` receives `cls` and can read/modify class state, while `@staticmethod` is a plain utility function with no awareness of the class.
- Python MRO (Method Resolution Order) with multiple inheritance — need to look into how `super()` resolves in diamond inheritance patterns.

